-- Western Union nearing $1 bln purchase of Travelex unit: report
-- 
-- Fri Jul 1, 2011 3:16pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2011/07/01/us-western-union-nearing-1-bln-purchase-idUSTRE76055I20110701

 

 (Reuters) - Western Union Co ( WU.N ), the world's largest payment transfer company, is in talks to buy a division of Apax Partners LLP's Travelex foreign-exchange business for about $1 billion, Bloomberg reported. 

 The deal to acquire Travelex's global business-payments unit may be announced as early as next week, the report said, citing people with knowledge of the matter. Travelex is the world's largest non-bank provider of foreign-exchange services to corporations, according to its website. Western Union declined to comment. (Reporting by  Brenton Cordeiro ; Editing by  Prem Udayabhanu )